Cell.Text: Another girl killed. This is Susanna, from Candlehearth Hall. | Served me a drink just a few nights ago... but I can't say I knew her.
Susanna's the third. It's always the same: young girl, killed at night, body torn up.

Cell.Text: [S] Look, there's a war going on, if you hadn't heard. We barely have enough soldiers to walk the streets, much less patrol every corner.

Node.Caption: MS11GuardInsinuations: Sounds like the guards aren't doing their job.

Cell.Text: [S] G|If you want to help, ask some of these gawkers if they saw anything useful. | I'm going to examine the body before the rats can get to it.

Node.Caption: MS11GuardWantHelp: Could you use some help?

Cell.Text: Same as the others. Looks like she was stabbed, and then cut apart. | It's like an animal got to her, but these are the wounds of a blade.
Just like always -- nobody saw anything useful. The bastard's escaped again.

[S] G|Look, friend, if you think you can do better than the legion of guards, be my guest. | You'll need to talk to Jorleif, though. We can't just let anyone go around claiming to be on official business. | If he's willing, then we'll talk.

Node.Caption: MS11GuardPlayerWantsToHelp: There might be more to this, if you'll let me help.

Cell.Text: [S] G|All right, then. | I noticed a trail of blood leading away from here. | Helgird's taken the body into the Hall of the Dead to prepare for burial. She's a little crazy, but if she knows anything, it's dead bodies.

Node.Caption: MS11CrimeSceneGuardHintTopic: Jorleif has granted me permission to aid in the investigation.

Cell.Text: Indeed. I... I thought you captured the Butcher. | You said the city was safe, now. How could this have happened?
[S] G|Obviously. You should visit the Bloodworks to talk to Wuunferth -- we need to figure out where the evidence went wrong.

Node.Caption: MS11SecondCrimeScenePointerToWuunferth: The killer must still be out there.

Cell.Text: Hold it there! Keep your distance.
[S] We're stretched thin as it is with the war. Nobody has the time to spend on this. Not pleasant, but it's the truth.
